gomodel:SYNGO_2900  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Endophilin 2, 3 and Arc Localize to Post-synaptic Sites with GluR1 in Hippocampal Neurons\"\n- \"Arc immuno-EM gold particles were present throughout the spine but were enriched over the postsynaptic density (PSD) where they appeared at, or very near, the plasma membrane (Figure 2B).\"\n- \"Consistent with EM localizations, Arc protein localized in DIV 21 hippocampal primary neurons to dendrites with puncta in spines, and colocalized with both the AMPAR subunit GluR1 and endophilin 3 (Figures 2C).\"\n\nSupplemental Figure S4A: \"Arc and Endophilin Associate with Endosomes in Neurons\"\n- \"When Arc was expressed individually, the transgene accumulates in dendrites with a uniform, dispersed distribution, and shows enrichment in dendritic spines (Supplemental Figure S4A)\". Experimental description: - Species of neurons not stated in the paper, but traced back to PMID:861729: \"Rat hippocampal neurons in dispersed cell culture\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2900" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

